it in my game, and I can't.

00:42:34.160 --> 00:42:36.530
But I'm sure if I had more
time, I could perfect it.

00:42:36.530 --> 00:42:39.050
Is it just that it's hard,
or maybe today the game's

00:42:39.050 --> 00:42:41.590
changed, where people are going
for and-ones and three-point

00:42:41.590 --> 00:42:42.449
plays?

00:42:42.449 --> 00:42:44.490
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: Thank
you for your question.

00:42:44.490 --> 00:42:45.550
It's not that hard.

00:42:51.860 --> 00:42:55.020
I think what's happening is that
the guys who are teaching kids

00:42:55.020 --> 00:42:56.760
to play the game--
kids, they don't

00:42:56.760 --> 00:42:59.690
want to work with their
back to the basket,

00:42:59.690 --> 00:43:01.830
close to the hoop,
where, actually, you

00:43:01.830 --> 00:43:03.000
get a high percentage shot.

00:43:03.000 --> 00:43:03.510
They don't want to do.

00:43:03.510 --> 00:43:05.210
That they want to
shoot three-pointers.

00:43:05.210 --> 00:43:08.570
Everybody wants to
shoot three-pointers.

00:43:08.570 --> 00:43:09.680
They see Stephen Curry.

00:43:09.680 --> 00:43:11.760
They say, oh, that's
what I want to do.

00:43:11.760 --> 00:43:15.900
And when I was
learning the game,

00:43:15.900 --> 00:43:21.082
guys that taught young
kids showed them post moves

00:43:21.082 --> 00:43:22.470
as part of the game.

00:43:22.470 --> 00:43:23.970
I had to learn post
moves, and I had

00:43:23.970 --> 00:43:26.600
to try to learn how to
play perimeter stuff,

00:43:26.600 --> 00:43:28.612
just so I understood the game.

00:43:28.612 --> 00:43:29.820
And that's not happening now.

00:43:29.820 --> 00:43:33.060
And everybody wants to
shoot three-pointers now.

00:43:33.060 --> 00:43:35.730
I'm the leading scorer
in the NBA, all-time,

00:43:35.730 --> 00:43:37.630
I made one three-pointer
in my whole career.

00:43:43.020 --> 00:43:45.850
And I can tell you that was a
shock and surprise to everybody

00:43:45.850 --> 00:43:49.320
that was there that night.

00:43:49.320 --> 00:43:51.060
But the ball bounced
out to the corner.

00:43:51.060 --> 00:43:52.980
I went out and got the rebound.

00:43:52.980 --> 00:43:55.530
And there was nobody coming
to guard me or anything,

00:43:55.530 --> 00:43:57.610
so I stepped back and shot one.

00:43:57.610 --> 00:44:00.220
And went in fortunately.

00:44:00.220 --> 00:44:02.990
I'm 1 for 13 in my
career in three-pointers.

00:44:02.990 --> 00:44:05.240
But I took a lot of
high percentage shots

00:44:05.240 --> 00:44:08.080
at the paint using my shot.

00:44:08.080 --> 00:44:09.610
And it worked.

00:44:09.610 --> 00:44:13.130
But kids, they don't want
to work on learning it.

00:44:13.130 --> 00:44:18.470
So I think styles go in cycles.

00:44:18.470 --> 00:44:20.400
So maybe at some
point, people will

00:44:20.400 --> 00:44:23.070
realize that getting
high percentage shots

00:44:23.070 --> 00:44:24.600
actually balances
out the guys that

00:44:24.600 --> 00:44:26.439
can make the three-pointers.

00:44:26.439 --> 00:44:27.480
And that's what you need.

00:44:27.480 --> 00:44:29.729
You need you need versatility
on the basketball court,

00:44:29.729 --> 00:44:34.480
because if you are stuck at
just making three pointers,

00:44:34.480 --> 00:44:36.700
you're going to end up
like the Warriors ended up

00:44:36.700 --> 00:44:40.900
this year, where once
Cleveland figured it out,

00:44:40.900 --> 00:44:44.400
